		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2"><a name="107102102474876"></a><span class="msgSubject">DON'T RUN in battle</span><br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: DON'T RUN in battle";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted: Dec  9th  2003 at  9:51pm EDT<span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=7;mid=107102102474876;num=24;page=1;post=1;replyto=107102102474876"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a>    </span></span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By: </span><a href="/db/poster.html?user=223345"><span class="">Kahia</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b><br />22 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Default  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=7;mid=107102102474876;page=1;howmany=50#107102102474876"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Hi ya'll, I just wanted to tell the pure caster classes, DON'T RUN! Us warriors (warrior to 42 agnostic, then deleted her so I could get the &quot;good armor&quot;, she's back up to 26)see this all the time. I've joked with my warrior husband that we should make a hotkey with /g %T STOP!! I'll get if off, but can't if you are running!!! We have /shield command at 30 which allows us to take part of your damage for 24 seconds AND still hit on the mob, etc. Pls, stay still and let us get the bad guys. Two more things. A heal, especially a CH (which we NEED!) WILL draw aggro, we will be more prepared to react if we know it's coming. Spam us, just so we know to start taunting and throw a /shield on you just in case. And, if you DO draw aggro for any reason and you let the warrior, pally or whomever get it off, wait at least a little bit before sitting down or it will go right back toward you. Taunt gives us (warriors) a + X (little amount) of hate. Meaning, if a cleric casts CH and it gives him/her 650 hate (I DO NOT know the numbers) and all the hitting I've been doing has garnered me 640, I hit taunt and have just A LITTLE more hate than you do. But, if it's a new pull and the cleric CH's from last fight or shammy slows or whatever, you are immediately at the top of the hate list. Taunt will give me +x hate over yours but sometimes it may take him a minute to realize it. In short, I...no, any good warrior, WILL get the mob off of you (unless we need to EVAC, where's the druid?), just don't run. =) Thanks for your time. <br />Tandacia Tyr <br />E`Ci Server <br /><a href="HTTP://www.guardians-of-order.com"></a> <br />PS-If I'm fighting something, or any warrior I know is in a fight and we get an add that goes for another, please bring it to us. Walk over to the tank with a /g get this off of me! or something. Many warriors, especially with a cleric in the group, have no problem fighting two. I love it! <br />PPS Sorry for the long post</p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Dream as if you'll live forever, Live as if you'll die today. ~James Dean</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td><td align="right" class="fs8" >24 replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
