<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Actually, if you CH at 40%, and the MT has gathered sufficient aggro, when the CH lands, the MT should still have aggro based on <br /> <br />a) low health aggro <br />b) tanking/taunt aggro <br /> <br />Only time I aggro on a CH is if we have more than one mob and the other mob has no one holding its aggro. And about the running around... just happens, because many clerics either don't have high HP/AC or they see they have aggro and run.</p>
