<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Being a 50th level cleric I couldn't agree more more with you.  When the mez breaks or the caster blasts to early or too much and get's run by a mob (usually a second mob) I jump in quickly with anything I can a DD or stun just to pull them off.  I know my HP/AC is low but pure casters are even lower and it's easier for me to take some damage than rez them.  I appreciate a tank who doesn't panic and start calling for a heal at 50%.  Don't worry I will keep you alive until I die.  Using CH is somewhat of a trial and error approach.  I usually like to know how many HP's my tanks have so I don't cast to early (or worse to late).  A CH is 400 mana and can heal thousands of HP's it truly is the best use of mana.  But clerics beware you will pull aggro with multiple mobs.  Make a hotkey so you tank knows a heal is coming and sit tight when the mobs rush you.  I've found that I can usually cast a HoT on myself to wheater the onslaught until the tank gets aggro back.  If clerics and tanks communicate well death can be avoided most of the time. <br />Celwenal Healur, 50th, The 7th Hammer</p>
