<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I'm pretty new to playing a cleric and to EQ in general, but one thing I picked up as useful recently was the spell Celestial Health.  It can never replace a good heal when ur tank is getting pounded heavily, but b/c it is a regen buff and not a &quot;heal&quot; persay, you don't get aggro from it.  I use this spell when the tank accidentally pulls multiple mobs, and it's saved our butts a few times. It isn't very mana efficient, but it you can you use it to heal one character b4 casting a heavy heal on another (with no aggro you can actually cast that heal). Anyways, that's all I have to say about that.</p>
