<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I agree with what has been said, even with the &quot;it happens&quot;.  I know I have done it a time or two.  When you start getting smacked for 400s per hit, you begin to panic even with AC of just under 1000. <br /> <br />The HoT line is a very good line, I use it with CHeal, Divine Light and Remedy.  Throw a HoT when the puller leaves to pull again, they appriciate the extra HPs that they receive while running to and from the Mobs and it shows that you are paying attention to the situation. <br /> <br />For casting CHeal, I start at 40% and then adjust from there.  There are times that--if you and your tank have nerves of steel--it is beneficial to keep the warrior around 35% health to gain the extra damage they do from being bezerk.  Don't do this with Pallys or SKs, they dont have the ability to bezerk at 35% health. <br /> <br />Also, keep either Divine Aura or Divine Barrier (DA has shorter cast time...its the one I use) memed at all times.  This give you an Invunerability and Neg Argo effect for 18 seconds, use the time to mem root, gate, a fast heal or such.  However, remember that you cannot cast or have spells cast upon you (both benificial and detrimental), so make sure the evac unit in the group knows to tell you to drop it...better if you do it yourself. <br /> <br />Best of all...Don't Run, if you do, realize it is just a game, rez your sorry butt and get back in there.  Have fun! <br /> <br />-Daineden Silverbeard <br />57th Templar of Brell <br />Nameless Server <br />Member of Clan Adept</p>
