<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>My warrior is 56 now, sitting at 6k raid buffed and 1100 ac.  Whenever i tank in PoValor(usually a lot) i tell clerics to hit me with a HoT around 60ish and CH around 40%.  I dont drop that fast as long as the mob is slowed by a sham/ench.  But I agree, running is the worst thing you can do, I've been grouped with a rogue who got agro from our MT (i was TT for then, was a raid)  And ran around like a headless chicken.  Our tank was a warrior, they cannot stun and cannot cast spells for agro like a sk/paladin.  The rogue needless to say, died in a few seconds as the tank couldnt even hit the mob with it running around his head.  Ive noticed that rangers do this alot as well, no offense but at level 62 you should be using your bow.  Not two agro weapons, he was using an SoD/CHoS...I was not able to take agro from him when he had on a FoS.  I feel sorry for him for dying, but when you snare the mob at 70ish %, you will get agro along with your weapons proccing stuns.</p>
