<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Okay, all this talk about CH this, CH that, once a cleric reaches level 68, CH aka hold onto your pantys for 10 seconds will be NO MORE!  Pious light is a 1.8 3700 HP heal that with AA's, can crit heal for well over 7k.  With the new HoT, Pious Elixir and this, I will ONLY cast CH when I am LOM, and by that level, mana pool should be well over 6k, so a quick heal of 700 mana will not be anything, given FT is maxed and you have a wonderful chanters Clairvoyance +20 mana spell.  And buying this wonderful things, called Concentration Elixirs are a big help.  About 90pp a swig but I will pay that much for saving my groups life and for sake of my rep not being a cleric that is always OOM.  And with druid 9, this only helps and by that level everyone should have a horse.  Never need to sit and stand and no more of that, begin casting CH and realize you need to stop, find your horse, click it off, Duck, with CH no longer a needed spell, you won't need any interrupting, therefore making a constant medding.  Lets do the math +20 mana medding, +20 mana CV, +15 max FT, +3 Concentration Potion, +9 Steeloak = 67 mana a tick, plus with Mind Wrack (300) and New Spiritual Ascendence (10) you can be medding as much as 377 mana a tick.  THAT is amazing, in two ticks you can med more than you took to cast that quick heal, so lets figure, 1.8 seconds to cast spell and 12 seconds to med up as much as you used to cast, that is 13.8, damn near the same amount of you would take to cast CH, only difference is the tank isn't dead and YOU and the rest of the group are alive, makes high level healing easier.  And at that level with a tank breaking 10k HPs, one cast at 40% will get him to full health and give you enough time to med to full only to cast again at 40, givin the local slower has half a brain.  Just a thing to look forward to for you lower level clerics.</p>
