<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>I agree the new cleric heals are awesome.  But I still have CH up in case the tank is needing a high number of quick heals and I have the chance to save some mana with CH in between (like at the end of a fight).  At 70 if you are lucky enough to get your new self buff you don't need Druid buff for mana regen -- cleric (self buff) and druid buff give same.  I haven't been lucky enough to get any 70 spells yet tho! Right now with my healing AA pre-omens maxed (haven't got all the omens aa yet), pious light crits for about a 10.5k heal and even without criting heals for over 5k.  That is one nice heal especially in combo with pious elixer which does 1170 heal per tick.  Having it extended two ticks with AA and the shawl means it heals over time for 7k+.  Still in zones like RS and MPG you will be using your fast heals on top of it.   <br /> <br />What I love though is the tanks that tell clerics how to heal and send me tells saying to use CH instead of my new fast heals.  I tell them 1) I am at 85-90 mana with my fast heals so don't worry about it and 2)I will decide which heal is best as I know how to heal!!! Only been playing this toon going on 5 years!</p>
