<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I have seen posts that speak of HoT spells and how they do not replace a good heal to tanks....Yes and No. <br /> <br />Personally, the low aggro generated from these is worth looking at. If you know the rate at which your tank is loosing HP on average, you can cast you HoT fairly early on to stabilize there Hp's....Depending on the DPS in the group, This sometimes is the only Heal i use. I rarely run out of mana even with chain pulling using this vs. complete healing. Granted, later on when mobs are hitting for some serious damage, CH will be the primary heal I will use BUT, I will still stablize the puller if adds come to ensure I can get the CH spell off. <br /> <br />So to recap, HoT spells I use to stabilize so healing the big guy with a lengthy cast time spell is a non issue.</p>
