<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=7;mid=107102102474876;page=1;howmany=50#1118952942498777505"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>My normal spell lineup includes the following: <br /> <br />Pious Remedy <br />Pious Light <br />Pious Elixir <br />Word of Vivification <br />Complete heal <br />Divine Intervention <br />Divine Aura <br />Divine Barrier <br />One slot that I swap out for buff, or keep yaulp in when horseless. <br /> <br />Yes, that's right, 5 different heals, and I use every single one of them.  <br /> <br />Remedy saves the casters, and is often spammed on the tank during raids.  <br /> <br />Light is a really good heal for patching melees, and healign the tank until slow hits. <br /> <br />Elixir is great if someone is taking ramp damage, or is being riposted, but is not tanking. It's also good for keeping a tank up during the initial pull, until slow hits, paired with fast heals.  <br /> <br />WoV heals the whole group, pretty mana heavy, but great if you are dealing with repeat AoEs.  <br /> <br />Complete heal, is critical for two things. First, there are the mobs that you need CH chains on. The ones that put out massive DPS, but take a while to kill. Even with a 9500mana pool, fast heals can empty my mana pretty quickly, and if the fight lasts 10-15 minutes, the raid is going to wipe.  <br /> <br />Second, CH is the absolute best heal to use, if you have a 15k+ tank, in a typical grind group, somewhere like riftseekers. Sure you can spam SL, but the two casts of SL that it takes to equal one CH, will eat your mana up pretty fast. Using CH, we can keep the statue room cleared, plus pull down to some of the other named, and not have mana problems. With SL, I'll run low mana, just keeping statue room clear.</p>
